## Dependencies & Execution Order

### User Story Dependencies

```
Setup (Phase 1)
    ↓
Foundational (Phase 2)
    ↓
    ├─→ US1: New User Registration (Phase 3) ← P1 Critical
    ├─→ US2: Existing User Login (Phase 4) ← P1 Critical
    │
    └─→ US3: View Task List (Phase 5) ← P2 High (depends on US1 or US2)
            ↓
            ├─→ US4: Create New Task (Phase 6) ← P2 High
            ├─→ US5: Edit Task (Phase 7) ← P3 Medium
            ├─→ US6: Delete Task (Phase 8) ← P3 Medium
            ├─→ US7: Toggle Completion (Phase 9) ← P3 Medium
            └─→ US8: User Logout (Phase 10) ← P2 High
                    ↓
                    └─→ Polish (Phase 11) ← Final phase
```

### Critical Path
1. **Phase 1 (Setup)** → MUST complete first - establishes project structure
2. **Phase 2 (Foundational)** → MUST complete before user stories - provides core infrastructure
3. **Phases 3-4 (US1-US2)** → Can be done in parallel - both are authentication flows
4. **Phase 5 (US3)** → Depends on authentication (US1 or US2) - displays tasks
5. **Phases 6-10 (US4-US8)** → Can be done in parallel after Phase 5 - all task operations
6. **Phase 11 (Polish)** → MUST complete last - enhances all features

